42
00:04:18.852 --> 00:04:20.745
[GRUNTS]

43
00:04:21.397 --> 00:04:23.833
[POUNDING AT DOOR]

44
00:04:23.857 --> 00:04:26.211
[PANTING]

45
00:04:26.235 --> 00:04:27.504
[DOOR CLATTERS OPEN]

46
00:04:27.528 --> 00:04:30.280
Morning. ma'am.

47
00:04:33.283 --> 00:04:34.995
What's wrong?

48
00:04:35.411 --> 00:04:37.389
Someone here to see you.

49
00:04:37.413 --> 00:04:40.393
[SOFT DRAMATIC MUSIC]

50
00:04:40.417 --> 00:04:44.230
♪ ♪

51
00:04:44.254 --> 00:04:45.538
Upstairs. boys.

52
00:04:47.215 --> 00:04:48.717
Morning. Bill.

53
00:04:50.635 --> 00:04:52.279
Shit.

54
00:04:52.303 --> 00:04:54.198
Yeah.

55
00:04:54.222 --> 00:05:01.205
♪ ♪

56
00:05:01.229 --> 00:05:04.918
- [GRUNTS]
- [HORSE WHINNIES]

57
00:05:04.942 --> 00:05:06.878
Mr. O'Hara.

58
00:05:06.902 --> 00:05:08.324
Mr. Mayor.

59
00:05:08.348 --> 00:05:10.767
I assume you know why I'm here.

60
00:05:12.908 --> 00:05:14.594
I've just come from the hospital

61
00:05:14.618 --> 00:05:16.830
where Chief Atwood is laid up.

62
00:05:17.907 --> 00:05:19.951
He's claiming you attacked him.

63
00:05:20.750 --> 00:05:22.060
Is that what he said?

64
00:05:22.084 --> 00:05:24.647
He didn't say anything.
His jaw is wired shut.

65
00:05:24.671 --> 00:05:26.607
But I have a written statement
to that effect.

66
00:05:26.631 --> 00:05:27.758
That's not what happened.

67
00:05:28.925 --> 00:05:31.070
Your former colleagues over there

68
00:05:31.094 --> 00:05:33.781
claim Chief Atwood
was inebriated on duty

69
00:05:33.805 --> 00:05:36.975
and fell down a flight of stairs.

70
00:05:38.940 --> 00:05:40.275
[CHUCKLES]

71
00:05:40.299 --> 00:05:42.801
Would you dispute their assertion?

72
00:05:45.108 --> 00:05:46.624
I...

73
00:05:46.944 --> 00:05:51.933
well... that does sound
like something he would do.

74
00:05:51.957 --> 00:05:54.749
Because I'm in need
of a new police chief.

75
00:05:55.328 --> 00:05:59.099
But you seem a little
worse for wear yourself.

76
00:05:59.123 --> 00:06:02.582
So the question is. are you up for it?

77
00:06:04.545 --> 00:06:08.300
♪ ♪

78
00:06:08.708 --> 00:06:11.696
I'm afraid I'll require
an answer immediately.

79
00:06:11.720 --> 00:06:15.700
♪ ♪

80
00:06:15.724 --> 00:06:17.417
Yes. sir.

81
00:06:18.894 --> 00:06:19.996
I'm your man.

82
00:06:20.020 --> 00:06:24.459
Good. You start today. Chief O'Hara.

83
00:06:24.483 --> 00:06:26.503
[SIGHS]

84
00:06:26.527 --> 00:06:28.171
Thank you. sir.

85
00:06:28.195 --> 00:06:32.510
♪ ♪

86
00:06:32.534 --> 00:06:34.160
What about Atwood. sir?

87
00:06:36.037 --> 00:06:37.848
If we can deport hundreds of Chinese.

88
00:06:37.872 --> 00:06:42.019
I'm sure we can rid ourselves
of one New York Protestant.

89
00:06:42.043 --> 00:06:43.562
[CANE TAPPING]

90
00:06:43.586 --> 00:06:47.149
♪ ♪

91
00:06:47.173 --> 00:06:49.485
[CHUCKLES]

92
00:06:49.509 --> 00:06:52.823
- Hyah!
- [HORSE WHINNIES]

93
00:06:52.847 --> 00:06:56.058
♪ ♪

94
00:06:57.351 --> 00:07:00.372
[CHICKENS CLUCKING]

95
00:07:00.396 --> 00:07:01.456
Hey.

96
00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:03.000
Sorry for bringing you here like this.

97
00:07:03.024 --> 00:07:05.168
It was the only safe place
I could think of.

98
00:07:05.192 --> 00:07:06.358
[SIGHS]

99
00:07:06.382 --> 00:07:08.195
What is it? What's wrong?

100
00:07:11.824 --> 00:07:13.636
I'll wait outside.

101
00:07:13.660 --> 00:07:15.037
Don't touch anything.

102
00:07:21.976 --> 00:07:23.310
From the latest batch of chop.

103
00:07:31.803 --> 00:07:34.306
There's nice detailing around the edges.

104
00:07:37.810 --> 00:07:40.331
It's clean cut. but I didn't...

105
00:07:40.355 --> 00:07:41.915
I didn't make this.

106
00:07:41.939 --> 00:07:44.501
Young Jun's guys are getting good.

107
00:07:44.525 --> 00:07:46.462
It's passable. It's not perfect.

108
00:07:46.486 --> 00:07:47.987
But it's close.

109
00:07:50.239 --> 00:07:52.950
You really think Young Jun's
gonna come after me?

110
00:08:01.752 --> 00:08:03.313
I don't want to find out.

111
00:08:03.337 --> 00:08:06.316
[TENDER MUSIC]

112
00:08:06.340 --> 00:08:08.818
♪ ♪

113
00:08:08.842 --> 00:08:10.862
You should come with me.

114
00:08:10.886 --> 00:08:15.742
♪ ♪

115
00:08:15.766 --> 00:08:17.214
I should.

116
00:08:17.238 --> 00:08:24.222
♪ ♪

117
00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:27.088
But you won't.

118
00:08:27.112 --> 00:08:31.008
♪ ♪

119
00:08:31.032 --> 00:08:32.885
I want to.

120
00:08:32.909 --> 00:08:39.916
♪ ♪

121
00:09:02.774 --> 00:09:04.902
Well. you better decide quick.

122
00:09:04.926 --> 00:09:11.933
♪ ♪

123
00:09:25.173 --> 00:09:28.176
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

124
00:09:38.061 --> 00:09:40.873
Hail to the goddamn chief!

125
00:09:40.897 --> 00:09:43.900
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

126
00:09:50.282 --> 00:09:51.468
Way to go. Chief.

127
00:09:51.492 --> 00:09:53.577
Well played.

128
00:09:56.914 --> 00:09:58.677
All right. all right. enough.

129
00:10:00.876 --> 00:10:02.604
Now back to work. you lazy cunts.

130
00:10:02.628 --> 00:10:04.689
[LAUGHTER]

131
00:10:04.713 --> 00:10:06.048
Congratulations. Bill.

132
00:10:07.424 --> 00:10:08.569
Long overdue.

133
00:10:08.593 --> 00:10:10.029
Thank you. Lee.

134
00:10:10.053 --> 00:10:13.056
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

135
00:10:31.409 --> 00:10:33.244
[SIGHS]

136
00:10:35.496 --> 00:10:38.475
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

137
00:10:38.499 --> 00:10:45.506
♪ ♪

138
00:10:48.592 --> 00:10:50.195
[INHALES SHARPLY]

139
00:10:50.219 --> 00:10:52.448
[GRUNTING]

140
00:10:52.472 --> 00:10:55.243
♪ ♪

141
00:10:55.267 --> 00:10:56.727
[CHUCKLES]

142
00:10:58.729 --> 00:11:00.164
Idiots.

143
00:11:00.188 --> 00:11:03.209
♪ ♪

144
00:11:03.233 --> 00:11:04.943
So you're going with her?

145
00:11:06.862 --> 00:11:08.280
I don't know.

146
00:11:10.615 --> 00:11:11.992
But you're thinking about it.

147
00:11:13.785 --> 00:11:15.288
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

148
00:11:16.873 --> 00:11:18.600
If you go with her.

149
00:11:18.624 --> 00:11:21.461
she won't be the only one
running from the Tongs.

150
00:11:22.962 --> 00:11:25.597
And if I stay. it's gonna get ugly.

151
00:11:26.007 --> 00:11:33.014
♪ ♪

152
00:11:38.729 --> 00:11:40.981
I don't belong in the Hop Wei anymore.

153
00:11:42.399 --> 00:11:44.234
You never really did.

154
00:11:46.362 --> 00:11:48.864
I can't tell you that
what's out there is better.

155
00:11:50.783 --> 00:11:52.201
It wasn't for me.

156
00:11:53.410 --> 00:11:55.847
But maybe it's time
to find out for yourself.

157
00:11:55.871 --> 00:12:02.879
♪ ♪

158
00:12:13.848 --> 00:12:15.242
Li Yong.

159
00:12:15.266 --> 00:12:16.893
What are they doing here?

160
00:12:19.020 --> 00:12:20.439
For protection.

161
00:12:24.402 --> 00:12:25.778
From me?

162
00:12:27.113 --> 00:12:29.699
I need to talk to you... alone.

163
00:12:32.410 --> 00:12:34.012
You can't be serious.

164
00:12:34.036 --> 00:12:36.014
Maybe we should talk another time.

165
00:12:36.038 --> 00:12:38.124
when you're not as angry.

166
00:12:41.127 --> 00:12:43.051
[CHOKING]

167
00:12:44.881 --> 00:12:51.346
♪ ♪

168
00:12:56.143 --> 00:12:59.122
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

169
00:12:59.146 --> 00:13:06.154
♪ ♪

170
00:13:14.912 --> 00:13:16.769
You think I would hurt you?

171
00:13:18.958 --> 00:13:20.769
I don't know.

172
00:13:20.793 --> 00:13:27.801
♪ ♪

173
00:13:45.486 --> 00:13:48.299
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

174
00:13:48.323 --> 00:13:52.053
♪ ♪

175
00:13:52.077 --> 00:13:54.480
They left her on my doorstep.

176
00:13:54.504 --> 00:13:57.298
♪ ♪

177
00:13:57.999 --> 00:13:59.310
[WHIMPERS]

178
00:13:59.334 --> 00:14:06.049
♪ ♪

179
00:14:07.050 --> 00:14:08.402
Oh. Lai.

180
00:14:08.426 --> 00:14:09.988
Lai.

181
00:14:10.012 --> 00:14:17.019
♪ ♪

182
00:14:31.535 --> 00:14:34.514
[INDISTINCT CHATTER. TOOLS CLATTERING]

183
00:14:34.538 --> 00:14:36.832
[PEOPLE GRUNTING]

184
00:14:42.754 --> 00:14:47.360
725.000 tons of steel and concrete

185
00:14:47.384 --> 00:14:48.886
taking the reach of American industry

186
00:14:48.910 --> 00:14:51.496
all the way to the Oregon
timberlands and back.

187
00:14:52.849 --> 00:14:55.411
Damn impressive sight. hmm?

188
00:14:55.435 --> 00:14:56.870
Sure.

189
00:14:56.894 --> 00:14:58.104
You don't agree?

190
00:14:59.689 --> 00:15:01.458
I do...

191
00:15:01.482 --> 00:15:04.044
which is why you might want
to start your hiring soon

192
00:15:04.068 --> 00:15:06.005
so you don't fall behind.

193
00:15:06.029 --> 00:15:07.089
What are you talking about?

194
00:15:07.113 --> 00:15:08.966
Now that Buckley's mayor.

195
00:15:08.990 --> 00:15:12.511
it won't be long till this lot's
on a slow boat back to China.

196
00:15:12.535 --> 00:15:14.054
[CHUCKLES]

197
00:15:14.078 --> 00:15:16.749
Even the mayor can't lower
the price of steel.

198
00:15:17.958 --> 00:15:19.686
Till the cost of materials comes down.

199
00:15:19.710 --> 00:15:21.688
I can't afford to hire American.

200
00:15:21.712 --> 00:15:23.275
You won't have a choice.

201
00:15:23.964 --> 00:15:26.401
Buckley's gonna outlaw Chinese labor.

202
00:15:26.425 --> 00:15:28.361
And who put Buckley in that seat?

203
00:15:28.385 --> 00:15:29.529
We did.

204
00:15:29.553 --> 00:15:31.698
Allowances will be made.

205
00:15:31.722 --> 00:15:34.200
Like I said. I have no use
for an honest mayor.

206
00:15:34.224 --> 00:15:35.910
Hold on.

207
00:15:35.934 --> 00:15:38.039
You promised me jobs. Mr. Strickland.

208
00:15:38.063 --> 00:15:40.651
I promised you a partnership.

209
00:15:40.899 --> 00:15:43.401
This is bigger than one job site.

210
00:15:43.777 --> 00:15:46.589
Every stop along my railroad
will create new towns.

211
00:15:46.613 --> 00:15:50.468
new opportunities for the men
whose interests you represent.

212
00:15:50.492 --> 00:15:53.971
I mean. real. lasting wealth.

213
00:15:53.995 --> 00:15:56.599
not the kind of backbreaking toil

214
00:15:56.623 --> 00:15:59.019
that chews up and spits out
every new wave of foreigners

215
00:15:59.043 --> 00:16:01.087
that wash up on American shores.

216
00:16:02.338 --> 00:16:03.899
You gave me your word.

217
00:16:03.923 --> 00:16:06.027
Your anger is misplaced.

218
00:16:06.509 --> 00:16:08.570
Man like you shouldn't have
to live in a bar.

219
00:16:08.594 --> 00:16:11.323
hustling work for ungrateful drunks.

220
00:16:11.347 --> 00:16:14.296
I'll make you the richest
Irishman in San Francisco.

221
00:16:14.320 --> 00:16:16.411
Then you'll have the power
to do whatever you please...

222
00:16:16.435 --> 00:16:17.704
invest in industry.

223
00:16:17.728 --> 00:16:20.006
hire as many barflies
as your conscience requires.

224
00:16:20.030 --> 00:16:21.396
My people need jobs now.

225
00:16:21.420 --> 00:16:24.796
Your people do half the work
for twice the pay.

226
00:16:24.820 --> 00:16:26.756
I don't want the Chinese here
any more than you do.

227
00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:28.716
but while they are here.
you better believe

228
00:16:28.740 --> 00:16:30.617
I'm gonna make a dollar off them.

229
00:16:32.327 --> 00:16:34.097
Now. if you're finished
waving your banner

230
00:16:34.121 --> 00:16:36.265
for the Emerald Isle. let's have a drink

231
00:16:36.648 --> 00:16:38.567
and talk about your future.

232
00:16:39.626 --> 00:16:41.145
I trusted you.

233
00:16:41.169 --> 00:16:43.273
[TENSE MUSIC]

234
00:16:43.297 --> 00:16:44.821
And you fucked me.

235
00:16:45.133 --> 00:16:47.029
If you really believe that.

236
00:16:47.510 --> 00:16:49.309
you aren't the man I thought you were.

237
00:16:49.333 --> 00:16:55.852
♪ ♪

238
00:17:06.822 --> 00:17:09.801
[PEOPLE GRUNTING]

239
00:17:09.825 --> 00:17:13.495
♪ ♪

240
00:17:21.045 --> 00:17:23.072
He's been like this for days.

241
00:17:23.589 --> 00:17:26.073
There must be something more
you can do for him.

242
00:17:26.676 --> 00:17:28.678
His blood is poisoned.

243
00:17:30.930 --> 00:17:33.868
There are some tinctures I can prepare

244
00:17:33.892 --> 00:17:35.727
to end his suffering.

245
00:17:37.771 --> 00:17:39.749
Get the fuck out.

246
00:17:39.773 --> 00:17:42.734
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

247
00:17:50.034 --> 00:17:53.680
[DOOR CLICKS OPEN AND SHUT]

248
00:17:53.704 --> 00:17:55.831
He's right. you know.

249
00:17:57.833 --> 00:18:00.127
There's nothing he can do.

250
00:18:02.630 --> 00:18:04.548
You're gonna be fine.

251
00:18:08.427 --> 00:18:10.073
You just need to rest.

252
00:18:10.097 --> 00:18:12.742
[LAUGHS]

253
00:18:12.766 --> 00:18:14.786
I'm about to get plenty of it.

254
00:18:14.810 --> 00:18:16.269
Don't talk like that.

255
00:18:17.813 --> 00:18:19.523
You've come back from worse.

256
00:18:23.819 --> 00:18:25.421
Look at me.

257
00:18:25.445 --> 00:18:26.950
Look at me.

258
00:18:27.846 --> 00:18:29.198
It's time.

259
00:18:29.223 --> 00:18:30.993
[SOMBER MUSIC]

260
00:18:31.243 --> 00:18:33.386
Don't let me go out a babbling old man

261
00:18:33.410 --> 00:18:34.888
pissing himself in public.

262
00:18:34.912 --> 00:18:36.598
What are you asking me to do?

263
00:18:36.622 --> 00:18:38.266
What you should have done

264
00:18:38.290 --> 00:18:40.227
when you first took over the Tong.

265
00:18:40.251 --> 00:18:41.669
Fuck that.

266
00:18:43.462 --> 00:18:46.066
I spent my entire life scrapping.

267
00:18:46.090 --> 00:18:47.859
I built something.

268
00:18:47.883 --> 00:18:51.238
I was the most powerful man
in Chinatown.

269
00:18:51.262 --> 00:18:54.432
That's how I want to be
remembered. not like this.

270
00:18:55.392 --> 00:18:57.936
You got what you wanted.

271
00:18:59.020 --> 00:19:01.054
Give me my dignity.

272
00:19:01.078 --> 00:19:02.834
I got what I wanted?

273
00:19:02.858 --> 00:19:05.169
♪ ♪

274
00:19:05.193 --> 00:19:09.257
All I wanted... was your respect.

275
00:19:09.281 --> 00:19:11.243
Then earn it.

276
00:19:11.950 --> 00:19:14.452
You are the leader of the Hop Wei.

277
00:19:15.120 --> 00:19:16.265
Act like it.

278
00:19:16.289 --> 00:19:22.753
♪ ♪

279
00:19:32.785 --> 00:19:34.287
What is it?

280
00:19:36.809 --> 00:19:38.621
I love you. Father.

281
00:19:38.645 --> 00:19:45.652
